# Cloudflare Pages routing for the APP project (repo root).
# The marketing site lives in marketing/ and deploys as its OWN Pages project (output dir
# = marketing), so this file does not affect it. Here, real static files (assets) serve
# directly; everything else falls back to the single-page app (index.html) so deep links /
# unknown paths still load the app.
# NOTE: this catch-all shadows standalone static .html files (they get rewritten to
# index.html), so in-app help pages are rendered as modals inside the app, not separate
# pages (see the geofence-guide modal). Do not add standalone static HTML here expecting
# it to serve — it won't.
/*    /index.html   200
